Mix wafer crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter; press onto bottom of 13x9-inch pan. Freeze 10 min. Beat cream cheese and remaining sugar with mixer until well blended. Spread carefully over crust; top with pineapple. Slice 4 bananas; arrange over pineapple. Beat pudding mixes and milk in medium bowl with whisk 2 min. Stir in 1 cup whipped topping; spread over banana layer in pan. Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate 5 hours. Slice remaining bananas just before serving; arrange over dessert. Top with chocolate curls.